&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team You’ll Work With&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We founded Carta LLC in 2019 with a mission to expand Carta’s total addressable market and acquire more nodes in the ownership graph outside Venture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carta LLC is Carta’s first step into alternative assets including Private Equity, Real Estate, Professional Services Organizations, Roll-ups, and other non-tech operating companies. To do this, Carta LLC must support the disparate equity structures, heavier reliance on documents, and multi-entity structures we see in these companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Implementations team is responsible for onboarding LLCs or PE-backed companies onto the Carta platform. The team utilizes their advanced equity knowledge with exceptional client and project management skills to onboard companies and their data on the Carta platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a demonstrated ability to solve ambiguous problems and offer creative solutions to meet customer needs. You possess a helpful and professional attitude and can exhibit diplomacy, tact, and poise under pressure when working through customer issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You care deeply, genuinely, and passionately about client services. You have great people skills and a high degree of empathy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proficient in Excel and have experience with CRMs (Preferably: Salesforce)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are able to quickly learn and understand our SaaS platform configuration and troubleshoot system issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong project management skills-must be able to manage multiple onboarding projects (40+) at a time, while providing timely follow up to clients. You are highly organized and can manage a group of C-Suite clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are familiar or will become familiar with Private Equity, Capitalization and LLC&lt;/li&gt;
