&lt;p&gt;You will be joining our Sales Operations team. Our Sales Operations team is a lean, agile group that supports 4 revenue lines and 200+ reps. You’ll be joining as a Sales Operations Manager focused on designing, enforcing, and improving sales processes and working on large cross-functional initiatives. The projects we tackle are broad, but a few examples would be segmentation and swim lanes, defining sales processes, or implementing a quote-to-cash system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Problems You&#39;ll Solve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Carta, our employees set out on a mission to unlock the power of equity ownership for more people in more places. We believe that the problems we solve today unlock the opportunities of tomorrow. As a Sales Operations Manager, you’ll work to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a business architect and project manager for requests to change or create new Sales processes. You will lead projects from start to finish ensuring successful completion, including gathering business requirements, designing processes, working with system admins to build these processes in our tools, and providing clear, concise documentation to train sales on any changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and use reporting as a tool to drive efficiencies and make informed decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operational pieces of new product rollouts – ensuring approvals, quoting, contracting, and reporting are working seamlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales Strategy on strategic initiatives including any changes to sales teams, segmentation, or swim lanes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, document, and enforce ROEs, including diplomatic mediation when there are swim lane disputes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
