&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team You&#39;ll Work With&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be joining our Web Presence team. In this role, you’ll be responsible for building and updating marketing web pages using our existing component library and CMS. You’ll execute on page briefs, address web tickets, ensure brand and design consistency, and support the rollout of new campaigns and content updates. This role requires strong attention to detail, solid HTML/CSS familiarity, and the ability to collaborate closely with designers, marketers, and engineers to deliver high-quality web experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detail-oriented: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll be responsible for translating page briefs into polished web experiences, ensuring content messaging is clear and every component looks and works exactly as intended.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer-centric: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll collaborate closely with marketers and designers to understand the “why” behind every request, ensuring each page meets user needs and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curious and thoughtful: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll ask the right questions to clarify briefs, identify missing information, and catch inconsistencies before they go live.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand-obsessed: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll ensure every page is aligned with our design system, brand standards, and accessibility best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Web expert: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ve built marketing pages before, know your way around HTML/CSS, and can navigate Contentful with confidence to bring content to life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accountable: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll manage web tickets with care, follow through on deadlines, and take pride in delivering high-quality work every time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicative&lt;/strong&gt;: You’ll proactively update stakeholders and teammates on the status of tasks and will escalate issues and blockers to keep projects moving forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building web pages in headless CMS recommended&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English language excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Disclosures:&lt;/p&gt;
